column169: XPO Logistics contacted ERTS regarding a product leak at an XPO drop lot. The release was approximately 1-gallon and impacted the wooden trailer floor in an 8’x6’ area. The Contractor cleaned-up the release with absorbent rags and overpacked the damaged drum. One drum of waste was generated from this incident. No storm-drains, waterways, or soil were impacted by this incident.

column169: XPO Logistics terminal UDV experienced a battery acid release from a 2113-pound battery. ERTS dispatched contractors to conduct cleanup operations. Contractors arrived onsite and confirmed approximately 10-gallons of battery acid released to a 6’ x 8’ area of the trailer floor and a 30’ x 2’ area of the concrete lot below due to improper loading; the battery fell over in transit. Absorbents and soda ash were worked into the impacted areas to clean and neutralize the release. All impacted absorbents, pallet pieces, and debris were then collected into (2) 55-gallon poly drums. The damaged battery was up righted and secured to a pallet. The waste was staged onsite for terminal personnel to manage.

column169: XPO-LOGISTICS contacted ERTS regarding a leaking lid on a 55-gallon poly drum containing SaniDate 5.0. The lid  appeared to be not sealed tight enough or not sealed correctly. This resulted in an estimated 1-cup release of product onto the top of the poly drum, the plastic shrink-wrap, and cardboard. A Contractor removed the  impacted plastic shrink wrap and cardboard and submerged them in water. The leaking drum was overpacked into a 95-gallon DF. In total, 2 drums of waste were generated for disposal. No storm-drains, waterways, or soil  were impacted by this incident.
